# GOD public-facing surface

These constraints apply to any file users will see when they open or fork the
repo (README, QUICKSTART, `.env.example`, output of `scripts/god.sh`, etc.).

## Branding

- User-visible content only refers to **GOD**, **Control Room**, **Backend**,
  **Agent Runtime**, **Pixel Town**.
- **Do not** surface `AgentSociety` or `JiuwenClaw` as primary subsystems. They
  may appear only inside an **Acknowledgements** / **Citation** section as
  upstream credit.
- Internal directories `agentsociety/` and `jiuwenclaw/` are implementation
  detail. Do not document them as the user-facing way to interact with GOD.

## Config namespace

- The only env namespace users configure is `GOD_*` (see `.env.example`).
- `scripts/god.sh` maps `GOD_*` to the internal `AGENTSOCIETY_*` /
  `JIUWENCLAW_*` variables. Never instruct users to set those directly.

## Recommended entrypoint

- The recommended command is `./scripts/god.sh start`. It is idempotent.
- `restart`, `new-run`, `stop`, `status`, `tail`, `open` are the public verbs.
- `factory-reset` is a hidden maintenance command — not in user docs.

## Excluded from public docs

Do not document any of the following in README/QUICKSTART:

- Screenshot-capture helpers or Playwright setup.
- Shell-not-found tips (e.g. `command not found: 1`).
- Generic port-conflict recipes that mention legacy ports.
- The internal `agentsociety/` and `jiuwenclaw/` directory layout.

## Files

```
README.md / README.zh-CN.md      # public; GitHub-launch style
QUICKSTART.md / QUICKSTART.zh-CN # public; minimal happy path
.env.example                     # only GOD_* keys
scripts/god.sh                   # only prints GOD vocabulary
AGENTS.md                        # internal agent guidance only
.cursor/rules/                   # internal agent rules only
```
